31
00:01:47,190 --> 00:01:48,780
{\an8}<i>Recalculating.</i>

32
00:01:48,858 --> 00:01:51,028
{\an8}<i>Turn right in .5 meters.</i>

33
00:01:51,111 --> 00:01:51,861
{\an8}Dad, no.

34
00:01:51,945 --> 00:01:53,605
{\an8}That takes us
into a construction site.

35
00:01:53,696 --> 00:01:55,946
Stupid kid thinks he's
smarter than a computer.

36
00:01:57,534 --> 00:01:59,454
Seat belts, kids.

37
00:01:59,536 --> 00:02:01,496
(tires squealing)

38
00:02:01,579 --> 00:02:03,669
(Homer wailing)

39
00:02:03,748 --> 00:02:06,748
{\an8}<i>Turn left. Turn right.</i>
<i>Turn left. Turn right.</i>

40
00:02:06,835 --> 00:02:09,295
(Homer moaning)

41
00:02:14,425 --> 00:02:17,465
<i>Decrease elevation ten feet,</i>
<i>then turn left.</i>

42
00:02:17,554 --> 00:02:18,814
D'oh!

43
00:02:20,014 --> 00:02:22,104
<i>You have reached</i>
<i>your destination.</i>

44
00:02:23,143 --> 00:02:24,853
{\an8}-Thanks for the ride.
-Bye, Dad!

45
00:02:24,936 --> 00:02:27,306
{\an8}<i>Turn right in 2.3 kilometers...</i>

46
00:02:27,397 --> 00:02:28,477
{\an8}Why, you...
(grunts)

47
00:02:28,565 --> 00:02:30,065
<i>Recalculating.</i>

48
00:02:30,150 --> 00:02:32,940
<i>-So cold. So cold.</i>
-(electronic crackling)

49
00:02:33,027 --> 00:02:35,067
(children laughing and shouting)

50
00:02:47,959 --> 00:02:48,959
{\an8}(squeaks)

51
00:02:50,712 --> 00:02:51,712
(swallows)

52
00:02:52,255 --> 00:02:53,835
Where's Mrs. K.?

53
00:02:53,923 --> 00:02:55,133
Mrs. Krabappel had
to go to Portland.

54
00:02:55,216 --> 00:02:56,376
Apparently, the
people she hired

55
00:02:56,467 --> 00:02:58,177
to deprogram her
sister from that cult

56
00:02:58,261 --> 00:03:00,141
turned out to be an
even worse cult.

57
00:03:00,221 --> 00:03:01,471
So, who's gonna
take her place?

58
00:03:01,556 --> 00:03:02,596
Me, I hope.

59
00:03:02,682 --> 00:03:04,732
Not you. Never you.

60
00:03:04,809 --> 00:03:06,309
And due to budget cuts,
until Edna comes back,

61
00:03:06,394 --> 00:03:07,734
I have no choice
but to merge

62
00:03:07,812 --> 00:03:10,112
the school's two
fourth grade classes.

63
00:03:10,190 --> 00:03:12,070
{\an8}-(students gasping)
-The other fourth grade?

64
00:03:12,150 --> 00:03:13,860
{\an8}But they're so different
from us.

65
00:03:13,943 --> 00:03:16,033
{\an8}They have music
on Tuesdays.

66
00:03:16,112 --> 00:03:18,782
{\an8}Their teacher
takes her shoes off.

67
00:03:18,865 --> 00:03:21,195
{\an8}Their twins are
one boy, one girl.

68
00:03:21,284 --> 00:03:22,914
Weird.

69
00:03:26,039 --> 00:03:28,039
{\an8}(sighs)
All right, new kids,

70
00:03:28,124 --> 00:03:31,134
{\an8}jam your chairs into
my kids' desks.

71
00:03:31,211 --> 00:03:33,341
{\an8}-Is anyone here?
-Oh, whatever.

72
00:03:33,421 --> 00:03:36,671
{\an8}-Is anyone here?
-Whatever.

73
00:03:36,758 --> 00:03:37,718
{\an8}-Is anyone here?
-Is anyone here?

74
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:38,760
{\an8}-Whatever.
-Whatever.

75
00:03:38,843 --> 00:03:39,973
{\an8}'Sup? I'm Bodhi.

76
00:03:40,053 --> 00:03:42,183
{\an8}-Do you surf?
-No.

77
00:03:42,263 --> 00:03:43,683
{\an8}My parents took me
to Hawaii once,

78
00:03:43,765 --> 00:03:45,095
{\an8}but I was intimidated

79
00:03:45,183 --> 00:03:46,643
{\an8}by the physiques
of the local kids,

80
00:03:46,726 --> 00:03:48,766
{\an8}so I just stayed
in the hotel room.

81
00:03:48,853 --> 00:03:49,903
{\an8}That's cool.

82
00:03:49,979 --> 00:03:51,649
{\an8}No, it's not cool.

83
00:03:51,731 --> 00:03:53,071
{\an8}(grunts)

84
00:03:54,817 --> 00:03:56,487
{\an8}You are so dead.

85
00:03:56,569 --> 00:03:58,739
{\an8}Sorry. Let me get
that for you.

86
00:03:58,821 --> 00:04:01,911
{\an8}(gasps)
You're blind.

87
00:04:01,991 --> 00:04:04,621
{\an8}If anyone messes with this
kid, I will destroy them.

88
00:04:04,702 --> 00:04:06,622
{\an8}It's okay. No one's
messing with me.

89
00:04:06,704 --> 00:04:07,754
{\an8}You're not a freak,

90
00:04:07,830 --> 00:04:09,830
{\an8}and I won't let you
think that about yourself.

91
00:04:09,916 --> 00:04:11,576
{\an8}I don't think
I'm a freak.

92
00:04:11,668 --> 00:04:13,378
{\an8}So brave.

93
00:04:13,461 --> 00:04:15,301
Hmm. Huh.

94
00:04:15,380 --> 00:04:17,670
{\an8}Um, this is the
last seat, so...

95
00:04:21,761 --> 00:04:24,471
{\an8}My side, your side.

96
00:04:24,555 --> 00:04:25,465
{\an8}Hi, Nikki.

97
00:04:25,556 --> 00:04:26,426
{\an8}I'm Bart.

98
00:04:26,516 --> 00:04:28,056
{\an8}This situation,
it's nuts, right?

99
00:04:28,142 --> 00:04:29,692
{\an8}Oh, look at you--

100
00:04:29,769 --> 00:04:31,939
{\an8}opening a book so you
won't have to talk to me.

101
00:04:32,021 --> 00:04:34,901
{\an8}Well, I'm just gonna be
tuning up the old armpit.

102
00:04:34,983 --> 00:04:36,033
{\an8}(blows tone)

103
00:04:36,109 --> 00:04:38,489
{\an8}(mimics sound
of passing gas)

104
00:04:38,569 --> 00:04:39,779
{\an8}Good news, children.

105
00:04:39,862 --> 00:04:42,282
{\an8}Everyone did well on this test,
except...

106
00:04:42,365 --> 00:04:44,525
{\an8}Lisa Simpson, F.

107
00:04:44,617 --> 00:04:45,577
An F?

108
00:04:45,660 --> 00:04:47,790
Okay, this is the time
when I always wake up.

109
00:04:47,870 --> 00:04:50,710
Come on, alarm clock,
get me out of this.

110
00:04:50,790 --> 00:04:53,630
(imitates blaring alarm)

111
00:04:53,710 --> 00:04:56,090
Sorry, Lisa--
this F is all too real.

112
00:04:56,170 --> 00:04:58,590
No it's not,
dream Hoover.

113
00:04:58,673 --> 00:05:00,933
{\an8}And as long as I'm asleep,
I'm gonna have some fun.

114
00:05:01,009 --> 00:05:01,969
I can fly!

115
00:05:02,051 --> 00:05:02,971
Wheeee!

116
00:05:03,052 --> 00:05:05,102
{\an8}(grunts, groans)

117
00:05:05,179 --> 00:05:06,889
{\an8}This isn't a dream.

118
00:05:06,973 --> 00:05:08,853
{\an8}I really did fail.

119
00:05:08,933 --> 00:05:10,393
{\an8}I take no joy in this.

120
00:05:10,476 --> 00:05:11,976
{\an8}(muttering):
Little Miss Perfect.

121
00:05:13,062 --> 00:05:14,652
BART:
Whoa.

122
00:05:14,731 --> 00:05:16,941
{\an8}Damn, this
caterpillar can eat.

123
00:05:17,025 --> 00:05:18,815
{\an8}(gasps) Damn.

124
00:05:18,901 --> 00:05:20,611
{\an8}Damn!

125
00:05:20,695 --> 00:05:22,355
Do you mind?

126
00:05:22,447 --> 00:05:25,867
Oh, man, you girls ruin
everything-- even vampires.

127
00:05:25,950 --> 00:05:28,290
Hey, vampires
are cool outsiders

128
00:05:28,369 --> 00:05:30,459
who love girls
who hate cheerleaders.

129
00:05:30,538 --> 00:05:32,708
No, they're all
about chomping neck.

130
00:05:32,790 --> 00:05:34,710
And they don't put
product in their hair

131
00:05:34,792 --> 00:05:35,842
like this loser.

132
00:05:37,628 --> 00:05:39,668
They look like this.

133
00:05:40,798 --> 00:05:42,678
NIKKI:
Awesome picture.

134
00:05:42,759 --> 00:05:44,179
Can I draw a robot
barfing screws

135
00:05:44,260 --> 00:05:45,930
on your arm with
my Sharpie?

136
00:05:46,012 --> 00:05:48,312
I... I'd like that.

137
00:05:50,933 --> 00:05:52,273
(laughing)

138
00:05:52,352 --> 00:05:55,192
And... finished.

139
00:05:58,358 --> 00:05:59,818
An F. An F!

140
00:05:59,901 --> 00:06:02,361
I hope Harvard never finds out
about this.

141
00:06:02,445 --> 00:06:04,485
(whirring)

142
00:06:07,241 --> 00:06:08,531
Huh?

143
00:06:08,618 --> 00:06:10,288
Can I teeter
while you totter?

144
00:06:10,370 --> 00:06:11,790
Ever since you got
that bad grade,

145
00:06:11,871 --> 00:06:13,411
you seem a lot cooler.

146
00:06:13,498 --> 00:06:15,748
Lisa, you want
to come skip rope?

147
00:06:15,833 --> 00:06:16,793
You can replace the tree.

148
00:06:16,876 --> 00:06:17,876
Eat lunch with me.

149
00:06:17,960 --> 00:06:19,050
Share my locker.

150
00:06:19,128 --> 00:06:20,758
Come to my
birthday party.

151
00:06:20,838 --> 00:06:22,758
Love me.

152
00:06:22,840 --> 00:06:25,130
Wow. This is kind of great.

153
00:06:25,218 --> 00:06:27,138
Lisa, can I speak
to you for a moment?

154
00:06:27,220 --> 00:06:28,220
Uh-oh.

155
00:06:28,304 --> 00:06:30,814
Looks like I'm in more trouble.

156
00:06:30,890 --> 00:06:32,060
(chuckles)

157
00:06:32,141 --> 00:06:33,981
Born to be bad.

158
00:06:34,060 --> 00:06:35,940
(children laughing)

159
00:06:36,020 --> 00:06:37,310
There was a mix-up
with your test.

160
00:06:37,397 --> 00:06:39,977
(sighs)
You got an A-triple-plus.

161
00:06:40,066 --> 00:06:41,816
Seems the F
belonged to Ralph.

162
00:06:41,901 --> 00:06:42,991
I cheated wrong.

163
00:06:43,069 --> 00:06:47,199
I copied the Lisa name
and used the Ralph answers.

164
00:06:49,409 --> 00:06:52,579
CHILDREN:
Gifted! Gifted! Gifted!

165
00:06:52,662 --> 00:06:53,912
I'm just advanced.

166
00:06:53,996 --> 00:06:55,116
You can catch up.

167
00:06:55,206 --> 00:06:56,576
CHILDREN:
Gifted!

168
00:06:57,750 --> 00:06:59,840
Dad, I know we don't normally
talk about this stuff,

169
00:06:59,919 --> 00:07:02,669
but there's this girl at school
I kind of like.

170
00:07:02,755 --> 00:07:05,755
Anyway, I'm really
hoping you could...

171
00:07:05,842 --> 00:07:07,012
Dad?

172
00:07:07,093 --> 00:07:08,093
-Hey, boy.
-(screams)

173
00:07:08,177 --> 00:07:09,257
(chuckles)
Your mother thinks

174
00:07:09,345 --> 00:07:10,925
I'm working on the car.

175
00:07:11,013 --> 00:07:13,433
Dad, that is genius,
but I need some advice.

176
00:07:13,516 --> 00:07:14,766
Homer?

177
00:07:14,851 --> 00:07:16,811
I thought you
were fixing my brakes.

178
00:07:16,894 --> 00:07:19,404
(panicked screaming)

179
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:21,270
But I need to talk
about man stuff.

180
00:07:21,357 --> 00:07:22,317
Talk to Grampa.

181
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:24,240
-He used to be a man.
-He did?

182
00:07:24,318 --> 00:07:25,948
(grunting)

183
00:07:26,028 --> 00:07:28,778
Give up the goods,
you yellow devil!

184
00:07:28,865 --> 00:07:31,115
So, I kind of like this girl
at school,

185
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:33,040
but I'm not sure
if she likes me back.

186
00:07:33,119 --> 00:07:35,619
There's one sure
way to find out

187
00:07:35,705 --> 00:07:38,745
if a girl likes
you-- steal a kiss.

188
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:39,923
Really?

189
00:07:40,001 --> 00:07:41,461
Did that ever work for you?

190
00:07:41,544 --> 00:07:42,424
Sure did.

191
00:07:42,503 --> 00:07:46,133
I remember it
like it was yesterday.

192
00:07:46,215 --> 00:07:48,465
(static crackling)

193
00:07:50,553 --> 00:07:51,393
Uh-oh.

194
00:07:56,184 --> 00:07:57,274
Whoa.

195
00:07:57,351 --> 00:07:59,191
She boards, too?

196
00:07:59,270 --> 00:08:06,240
♪♪

197
00:08:18,956 --> 00:08:25,956
♪♪

198
00:08:32,929 --> 00:08:34,389
So...

199
00:08:34,472 --> 00:08:36,182
what should we do now?

200
00:08:37,016 --> 00:08:38,846
Kiss her, ya idjit!

201
00:08:40,811 --> 00:08:41,941
(sighs)

202
00:08:42,730 --> 00:08:43,610
(shrieks)

203
00:08:43,689 --> 00:08:46,819
Bart Simpson kissed me.

204
00:08:46,901 --> 00:08:49,861
Oh, my God,
and that was my first kiss.

205
00:08:49,946 --> 00:08:52,736
It will always be my first kiss.

206
00:08:52,823 --> 00:08:54,123
Ew.

207
00:08:58,913 --> 00:08:59,913
Say, "Haw-haw."

208
00:08:59,997 --> 00:09:01,167
Haw-haw.

209
00:09:01,249 --> 00:09:03,419
That was great!

210
00:09:03,501 --> 00:09:05,501
Really great!

211
00:09:08,839 --> 00:09:12,389
♪♪

212
00:09:13,636 --> 00:09:16,306
Marge, Homer, this is Brody
and Madison McKenna.

213
00:09:16,389 --> 00:09:18,809
Bart has been sharing a desk
with their daughter, Nikki.

214
00:09:18,891 --> 00:09:21,691
Earlier today, your son
engaged in inappropriate

215
00:09:21,769 --> 00:09:24,229
mouth-on-mouth contact
with our daughter.

216
00:09:25,356 --> 00:09:27,476
You mean, he kissed her?

217
00:09:27,567 --> 00:09:29,687
On the top
of the slide.

218
00:09:29,777 --> 00:09:30,987
That's all
that happened?

219
00:09:31,070 --> 00:09:32,410
And I got to miss work?

220
00:09:32,488 --> 00:09:34,568
(chuckles):
Oh, I could kiss you.

221
00:09:34,657 --> 00:09:36,697
Mr. Simpson,
I'm an attorney,

222
00:09:36,784 --> 00:09:39,124
and my husband is
a federal prosecutor,

223
00:09:39,203 --> 00:09:40,833
and neither of us is happy.

224
00:09:40,913 --> 00:09:43,043
Well, maybe you guys
should look for easier jobs.

225
00:09:44,041 --> 00:09:45,791
Unless you make this

226
00:09:45,876 --> 00:09:47,336
an affection-free
environment,

227
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:49,630
we will sue this school
for its last dime.

228
00:09:49,714 --> 00:09:51,264
All right, here it is.

229
00:09:51,340 --> 00:09:53,260
And we will make <i>you</i>
regret the day

230
00:09:53,342 --> 00:09:54,642
your son was born.

231
00:09:54,719 --> 00:09:56,349
You're halfway home, lady.

232
00:09:59,807 --> 00:10:00,977
It's not my fault.

233
00:10:01,058 --> 00:10:02,688
Grampa told me to kiss her.

234
00:10:02,768 --> 00:10:05,348
Why didn't you just tell
him to club her on the head

235
00:10:05,438 --> 00:10:07,058
and drag her into a cave?

236
00:10:07,148 --> 00:10:09,278
You mean second base?

237
00:10:09,358 --> 00:10:11,278
Whoa, he's a little
young for that.

238
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:13,110
Well, if I talk to Nikki,
I'm sure I can...

239
00:10:13,195 --> 00:10:15,105
No! If you go near her
one more time,

240
00:10:15,197 --> 00:10:16,447
we'll be sued
into the poor house

241
00:10:16,532 --> 00:10:18,082
and have to eat
garbage forever.

242
00:10:18,159 --> 00:10:18,909
That's no problem.

243
00:10:18,993 --> 00:10:20,703
Mom can make garbage
taste great.

244
00:10:20,786 --> 00:10:21,946
Thank you.

245
00:10:22,038 --> 00:10:23,118
Well, I mean it.

246
00:10:23,205 --> 00:10:25,825
And it means
the world to me.

247
00:10:25,916 --> 00:10:27,246
Well, don't worry, boy.

248
00:10:27,335 --> 00:10:30,495
I know a wholesome way
to take your mind off girls.

249
00:10:30,588 --> 00:10:32,378
(screaming)

250
00:10:32,465 --> 00:10:34,085
This is awesome!

251
00:10:34,175 --> 00:10:36,135
If only real life
was in 3-D.

252
00:10:36,218 --> 00:10:37,798
(chuckles)
And the glasses smell

253
00:10:37,887 --> 00:10:40,097
like the last guy who
wore them had pizza.

254
00:10:42,850 --> 00:10:49,860
♪♪

255
00:10:58,908 --> 00:10:59,908
(grunts)

256
00:11:00,451 --> 00:11:07,461
♪♪

257
00:11:16,133 --> 00:11:18,223
(yelling)

258
00:11:18,302 --> 00:11:21,432
(yell echoing)

