on kissing, just keep laughing.

324
00:14:12,726 --> 00:14:18,606
(laughter continues)

325
00:14:18,691 --> 00:14:19,901
(laughter fading)

326
00:14:25,781 --> 00:14:26,991
(Bart sighs)

327
00:14:27,074 --> 00:14:28,874
Maybe I did do something wrong.

328
00:14:30,953 --> 00:14:31,753
(yells)

329
00:14:31,829 --> 00:14:34,869
Oh, Bart, I hate
to see you like this.

330
00:14:34,957 --> 00:14:36,787
(sighs)

331
00:14:36,876 --> 00:14:38,956
Aw, look who's all confused.

332
00:14:39,044 --> 00:14:40,384
Huh?

333
00:14:44,592 --> 00:14:46,052
What the hell
are you doing?

334
00:14:46,135 --> 00:14:47,385
I'm kissing you, stupid.

335
00:14:47,469 --> 00:14:49,309
You're the biggest
psycho I ever met.

336
00:14:49,388 --> 00:14:50,428
You wanna stop?

337
00:14:50,514 --> 00:14:51,774
Absolutely not.

338
00:14:51,849 --> 00:14:52,809
(sighs)

339
00:14:55,019 --> 00:14:57,479
(Willie humming)

340
00:14:57,563 --> 00:14:59,943
(groaning)

341
00:15:04,236 --> 00:15:05,146
(gasps)

342
00:15:05,237 --> 00:15:07,277
A VH-60N Whitehawk!

343
00:15:08,490 --> 00:15:13,830
(thrilling music plays)

344
00:15:13,913 --> 00:15:15,253
(children gasping)

345
00:15:18,959 --> 00:15:21,669
First Lady
Michelle Obama?

346
00:15:21,754 --> 00:15:22,674
(spits)

347
00:15:27,134 --> 00:15:29,184
I flew in from Turkmenistan

348
00:15:29,261 --> 00:15:32,431
because there's
a wonderful young person here

349
00:15:32,514 --> 00:15:34,644
who's feeling
a little discouraged.

350
00:15:34,725 --> 00:15:36,015
I sure am!

351
00:15:36,101 --> 00:15:37,651
This young lady...

352
00:15:37,728 --> 00:15:38,688
Oh.

353
00:15:38,771 --> 00:15:40,861
...thinks just because
she's a high achiever,

354
00:15:40,940 --> 00:15:42,440
no one will ever like her.

355
00:15:42,524 --> 00:15:43,534
Huh?

356
00:15:43,609 --> 00:15:44,739
Well, as I tell schoolchildren

357
00:15:44,818 --> 00:15:47,818
all over the world,
I was a high achiever.

358
00:15:47,905 --> 00:15:51,235
I got A's back
when A's were hard to get.

359
00:15:51,325 --> 00:15:53,945
I was just like Lisa Simpson.

360
00:15:54,036 --> 00:15:55,286
(gasps)

361
00:15:55,371 --> 00:15:56,751
That's right, Lisa.

362
00:15:56,830 --> 00:16:00,130
As an avid organic gardener,
I've read your blog.

363
00:16:00,209 --> 00:16:05,259
Flotus1 is First Lady
of The United States one!

364
00:16:05,339 --> 00:16:08,009
Yes. I wanted just "Flotus,"
but someone had it.

365
00:16:08,092 --> 00:16:11,142
That's me, 'cause I swim
with my flotuses on.

366
00:16:11,220 --> 00:16:14,220
Everything I have
I got through academics.

367
00:16:14,306 --> 00:16:17,226
I went to Chicago's
first magnet high school,

368
00:16:17,309 --> 00:16:19,979
then Princeton,
then Harvard Law.

369
00:16:20,062 --> 00:16:23,692
And now you're the most elegant
and popular woman in the world!

370
00:16:23,774 --> 00:16:24,944
Well...

371
00:16:25,025 --> 00:16:26,525
(laughing) I don't
know about that.

372
00:16:26,610 --> 00:16:28,820
There's Carla Bruni,
Queen Noor of Jordan...

373
00:16:28,904 --> 00:16:31,204
They're nothing compared to you.

374
00:16:31,281 --> 00:16:32,741
It's not a contest.

375
00:16:32,825 --> 00:16:35,325
But if it were, I think
we know how it would go.

376
00:16:35,411 --> 00:16:39,461
But before I was who I am today,
I was a nerd.

377
00:16:39,540 --> 00:16:41,170
So the lesson is, children...

378
00:16:41,250 --> 00:16:42,880
I'll tell them
what the lesson is.

379
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:44,090
He's our Joe Biden.

380
00:16:44,169 --> 00:16:45,709
Understood. So kids,

381
00:16:45,796 --> 00:16:48,876
be nice to Lisa,
because the overachievers

382
00:16:48,966 --> 00:16:51,086
will someday
be running the country,

383
00:16:51,176 --> 00:16:53,216
and you don't want them
to be too screwed up.

384
00:16:53,303 --> 00:16:55,603
Now, who else is
an overachiever?

385
00:16:55,681 --> 00:16:56,681
Come on, now!

386
00:16:58,017 --> 00:16:58,847
I am.

387
00:16:59,476 --> 00:17:00,556
I am, too.

388
00:17:00,644 --> 00:17:02,354
Fifth in my class
at Annapolis.

389
00:17:02,438 --> 00:17:04,148
Scaled the summit
of the highest peaks

390
00:17:04,231 --> 00:17:05,901
on six of seven continents.

391
00:17:05,983 --> 00:17:07,993
Hey, that's great.

392
00:17:08,068 --> 00:17:09,738
Don't forget to
bring the scooper

393
00:17:09,820 --> 00:17:11,070
when you
walk the dog.

394
00:17:11,155 --> 00:17:12,525
Ma'am, yes, ma'am!

395
00:17:12,614 --> 00:17:13,624
Now, let's roll.

396
00:17:14,616 --> 00:17:15,736
(grunting)

397
00:17:15,826 --> 00:17:16,786
Sorry, ma'am.

398
00:17:16,869 --> 00:17:19,249
